# Copy to .env and set your API base URL (no trailing slash, no `/api` suffix).
#
# Port 5279 is shared by FinanceApp.Web and FinanceApp.API (Mobile profile). If the *web*
# app is listening on 5279, /api/... requests hit MVC and return HTTP 404. For mobile, run
# FinanceApp.API (--launch-profile Mobile), or point EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL at the API on 5022:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5022
#
# 1. Start the API so it listens on all interfaces (required for phone/simulator):
#    From repo root: dotnet run --project FinanceApp.API --launch-profile Mobile
#    This uses port 5279 (http://0.0.0.0:5279).
#
# 2. Set EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL:
#
#    Physical device (same Wi‑Fi as computer):
#      Use your computer's IP, e.g. EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.100:5279
#      Mac/Linux: ifconfig | grep "inet "   Windows: ipconfig
#
#    iOS Simulator (runs on the Mac — prefer loopback; same Wi‑Fi is irrelevant):
#      EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5279
#      If that fails, try your Mac's LAN IP (must match API bind + firewall):
#      EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.x.x:5279
#
#    Android Emulator:
#      EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:5279
#
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.100:5279
